ZH: 我们需要保持虔诚的心态去修行。
EN: We need to maintain a devout attitude in our practice.

ZH: 这位老人是个虔诚的信徒，每天都会去教堂祷告。
EN: The old man is a devout believer who goes to the church to pray every day.

ZH: 在这个节日里，人们会展示他们对神灵的虔诚。
EN: During this festival, people display their devotion to the deities.

ZH: 这个神庙吸引了很多虔诚的朝圣者。
EN: This temple attracts numerous devout pilgrims.

ZH: 她一直生活在虔诚的宗教家庭中。
EN: She has lived in a devout religious family her entire life.

ZH: 他每天都用虔诚的心灵去面对挑战。
EN: He faces challenges every day with a devout spirit.

ZH: 他虔诚地跟随着上帝的教导。
EN: He devoutly follows the teachings of God.

ZH: 她是一个虔诚而谦逊的人，总是乐于助人。
EN: She is a devout and humble person who is always willing to help others.

ZH: 我对穆斯林的虔诚和坚定信仰表示敬意。
EN: I admire the devoutness and steadfast faith of Muslims.

ZH: 她向家族传承了虔诚的信仰观念。
EN: She has passed down the devout beliefs of her family.

ZH: 这位僧侣经过多年的修行变得非常虔诚。
EN: The monk has become extremely devout after years of practice.

ZH: 他用虔诚的心向佛祖祈求健康和平安。
EN: He prays to the Buddha with a devout heart for health and peace.

ZH: 虔诚的人普遍有平和的内心和善良的品格。
EN: Devout people generally have a peaceful heart and kind character.

ZH: 我在教堂里遇到了一个非常虔诚的修士。
EN: I met a very devout monk in the church.

ZH: 她的虔诚来自内心的信仰和灵性的追求。
EN: Her devoutness stems from her deep faith and spiritual pursuits.

ZH: 虔诚的信徒相信祈祷有强大的力量。
EN: Devout believers believe that prayers have great power.

ZH: 他们来到此地是为了向虔诚的我们学习。
EN: They came here to learn from us, who are devout.

ZH: 虔诚的人会积极参与宗教活动。
EN: Devout people actively engage in religious activities.

ZH: 虔诚的教徒们每周都会去教堂参拜。
EN: Devout worshipers go to the church every week to worship.

ZH: 虔诚的信仰让他们觉得内心平静安宁。
EN: Devout faith gives them a sense of inner peace.
